UDM leader, Bantu Holomisa reacts to this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Nelson Mandela Bay's Mongameli Bobani has been removed as mayor. The United Democratic Movement's Bobani had previously survived five motion of no confidences. The motion of no confidence was brought by the ANC and DA. READ: Bobani survives another motion of no confidence “[Mongameli] Bobani, as we speak, is no longer the mayor of Nelson Mandela [Bay],” said UDM leader Bantu Holomisa. Bobani has been accused of corruption and mismanagement. He has denied any wrongdoing.